<div id="pageLeftSide"><h1  class="articleHeader">Bank Bailout To Add up to £1.5 trillion to Public Debt</h1><table id="articleInfo" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr valign="bottom"><td>by <b>Charlotte Cardingham</b></td><td rowspan="2" id="headerIcons"><a href="http://twitter.com/home/?status=RT+%40moneycouk+Bank+Bailout+To+Add+up+to+1.5+trillion+to+Public+Debt http://money.co.uk/t/tzP" onclick="return loadShareWindow(this.href);"><img src="http://serv01.money-resources.co.uk/images/common/button-retweet.gif"></a><a href="http://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?u=http://www.money.co.uk/article/1002877-bank-bailout-to-add-up-to-1-5-trillion-to-public-debt.htm" onclick="return loadShareWindow(this.href);"><img src="http://serv01.money-resources.co.uk/images/common/button-fshare.gif"></a></td></tr><tr><td valign="top">Published on 19 February 2009</td></tr></table><div id="pageTags"><div id="relatedSubjects">Related Subjects: </div><div id="relatedSubjectsTags"></div><div style="clear:left;"></div></div><div id="articleContent"><div id="articleImage"><img alt="Bank Bailout To Add up to £1.5 trillion to Public Debt" height="139" width="210" src="http://serv01.money-resources.co.uk/images/article/size3_210/black_and_white_twenties.jpg"></div><p id="articleIntroduction">New estimates suggest the government's recent bailout of RBS and Lloyds TSB will cost the tax payer up to £1.5 trillion.</p><p>The UK Government&rsquo;s recent bailout of struggling financial giants <a href="/companies/Royal-Bank-of-Scotland.htm">Royal Bank of Scotland</a> and <a href="/companies/Lloyds-TSB.htm">Lloyds TSB</a> looks set to add between &pound;1 trillion and &pound;1.5 trillion to national debt, figures out today have revealed.</p>
<p>More shocking still, this colossal intervention represents the equivalent of between 70% and 100% of Britain&rsquo;s GDP (gross domestic product).</p>
<p>The data, released today by the Office of National Statistics, paints a sorry picture of the UK&rsquo;s economy with public sector net debt already at a record high of &pound;703.4billion, or 47.8% of GDP, in January.</p>
<p>So far this financial year Government borrowing has totalled &pound;67.2billion, a figure that&rsquo;s almost three times higher than the &pound;23.1billion recorded at the same time last year.</p>
<p>The ONS decided to incorporate the financial impact of the bailed-out banks to the Government&rsquo;s books in their analysis of public sector finances as &quot;the Government has the ability to control the respective banks&rsquo; general corporate policy through the conditions associated with the agreements signed relating to recapitalisation.&quot;</p>
<p>However, while the &lsquo;official&rsquo; figures offer a not entirely unexpected snapshot of the UK&rsquo;s fiscal status, to some extent they do over exaggerate the dismal state of the economy.  Primarily this is because the ONS only balanced the Government&rsquo;s liquid assets in relation to their liabilities within their calculations, discounting their capital assets so as to reflect their ability to cover current debts in the short term.</p>
<p>The government now own a 68% stake in RBS and 43% stake in Lloyds TSB respectively.</p>
<p><em><a target="_blank" rel="nofollow" href="http://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/newsbysector/banksandfinance/4697046/Government-stakes-in-RBS-and-Lloyds-could-add-1.5-trillion-to-UK-national-debt.html">Source</a></em></p></div><form method="post" action="https://my.money.co.uk/signup.htm"><input type="hidden" name="email_subscribe" value="true" /><div style="background-image:url('/images/common/email-signup-article-background.gif'); padding:15px; height:141px; margin-bottom:15px; margin-top:5px; font-family:'Georgia'; color:#1F435D; background-repeat:no-repeat; width:587px;"><div style="font-size:20px; padding-bottom:9px;"><span style="color:#D71F00;">Get more  deals like this every week.</span></div><div style="font-size:18px; padding-bottom:7px;">Enter your email and name below to join over 530,000 other members who benefit from our invaluable deals each week.</div><div style="float:left; padding-right:15px; "><div style="font-family:Arial; color:#000; font-size:14px; padding-bottom:3px;">your email</div><input type="text" name="register_email" style="border:1px solid #E16601; font-size:18px; width:200px;"></div><div style="float:left; padding-right:15px; "><div style="font-family:Arial; color:#000; font-size:14px; padding-bottom:3px;">first name</div><input type="text" name="register_first_name" style="border:1px solid #E16601; font-size:18px; width:150px;"></div><div style="float:left; padding-top:12px;"><input type="image" src="/images/common/email-signup-article-button.gif" alt="Sign Up" /></div></div></form><script type="text/javascript">
